  [Text] Beijing, June 16 (XINHUA) -- Premier Li Peng will 
pay official visits to the Republic of Austria, the Federal 
Republic of Germany and Romania form June 29 to July 12, a 
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman announced at a weekly press 
conference here this afternoon. 
  According to the spokesman, the Chinese premier will pay 
visits to the three above countries at the invitation of 
Austrian Prime Minister Franz Vranitzky, German Chancellor 
Helmut Kohl, and Romanian President Ion Iliescu and Prime 
Minster Nicolae Vacaroiu. 

