<H3> <TI>   Moscow Criticizes U.S. Sanction Proposal on DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Criticizes U.S. Sanction Proposal on DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1606141594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1322 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1606141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 16 (XINHUA) -- Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev said today the U.S. draft resolution on 
phased UN sanctions against the Democratic People's Republic of 
Korea (DPRK) contradicts an earlier agreement reached between 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin and U.S. President Bill Clinton. 
  The document was distributed at the United Nations Security 
Council by the United States on Wednesday [15 June]. 
  Kozyrev told reporters that he was confused by the fact that 
"American diplomats had distributed in New York a draft 
resolution containing a concrete list of sanctions" against DPRK. 
  The U.S. move was made contrary to the "absolutely clear" 
agreement reached in a telephone conversation between Yeltsin 
and Clinton, as well as between their foreign ministers "to act 
jointly, to work on the draft resolution together and not to 
make unilateral initiative," Kozyrev pointed out. 
  He stressed that "in any case we shall not support the set 
of 
sanctions proposed without a preliminary agreement with us." 

</TEXT>

