<H3> <TI>   Russia, Vietnam Fail To Sign Bilateral Treaty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia, Vietnam Fail To Sign Bilateral Treaty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1606144094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1336 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1606144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 16 (XINHUA) -- Russian Prime Minister 
Viktor Chernomyrdin and his visiting Vietnamese counterpart Vo 
Van Kiet failed to sign the treaty on friendly relations on 
Thursday [18 June] because of contradictions over several 
issues, the ITAR- TASS NEWS AGENCY reported. 
  It said the disputed issues include prospecting and 
production of oil and natural gas by joint "Vietsovpetro" 
venture, the problems of the Vietnamese community in Russia and 
the Russian naval base in Vietnam's Cam Ranh. 
  The Vietnamese premier, who arrived in Moscow on Wednesday 
for a three-day official visit, held talks with Chernomyrdin on 
Thursday morning. He is also expected to meet with Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin. The sides were planned to sign a 
package of documents including, originally, the treaty. 
[sentence as received] 

</TEXT>

