<H3> <TI>   Delegate Outlines Beijing's Peaceful Space Efforts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegate Outlines Beijing's Peaceful Space Efforts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706023294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0203 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1706023294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, June 16 (XINHUA) -- The 37th session of the 
UN Committee on the Peaceful Uses of Outer Space ended here 
today. 
  China, as a member of the committee, was represented and the 
head of its delegation, Chen Shiqiu, addressed the meeting. 
  In his speech Chen outlined the efforts and achievements 
made 
by China in the peaceful uses of outer space and in the 
development of space science and technology, stressing that 
there should be international cooperation on the uses of outer 
space. 
  Delegates from various countries expressed a keen interest 
in 
an Asia-Pacific economic and social council ministerial meeting 
to promote the region's uses of outer space, which is scheduled 
for September in Beijing, as well as in the creation of an 
organization to oversee the uses of outer space in the region. 
  The committee now has 53 member nations and the meeting, 
which opened on June 6, is the first of its kind since the UN 
Outer Space Affairs Division was transferred here from New York. 

</TEXT>

