<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Holds Talks With Jimmy Carter </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Holds Talks With Jimmy Carter </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1606141494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1351 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1606141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 16 (XINHUA) -- The President of the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) Kim Il-song met 
here today with former United States President Jimmy Carter and 
his wife. 
  Local press reported that they held talks in a cordial 
atmosphere, but did not disclose details. 
  Carter's visit to the DPRK is aimed at facilitating 
exchanges 
of views on the nuclear issue which is currently taxing the 
United States, South Korea and the DPRK. 
  Carter, who is on a private tour on the Korean peninsula, 
met 
with South Korean President Kim Yong-sam before arriving in the 
DPRK. 
  He is scheduled to end his visit to the DPRK on Saturday [18 
June] and travel to South Korea by way of the truce village of 
Panmunjon before returning to the U.S. 

</TEXT>

