<F P=103> OW1606194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, June 16 (XINHUA) -- Iraqi President Saddam 
Husayn received here today Chinese Assistant Foreign Minister 
Wang Changyi and held talks with him on friendly Sino-Iraqi 
relations and regional and international issues of common 
interest. 
  The Chinese official, who is currently on a visit to Iraq, 
conveyed Chinese leaders' regards to Saddam Husayn and said that 
the Chinese Government attaches importance to consolidating and 
developing relations with Iraq. 
  Saddam, who is also Iraqi prime minister, asked the Chinese 
assistant foreign minister to convey his regards to Chinese 
leaders. 
  He voiced his hope that the friendly relations and 
cooperation between Iraq and China will develop and continue. 
  He gave an account of Iraq's position on the U.N. Security 
Council resolutions concerning the Gulf issues. 
  The Chinese official reiterated that China stands for the 
implementation of the U.N. Security Council resolutions, 
including gradually lifting the embargo according to that 
implementation. 
  Wang arrived here on June 14 on a working visit to Iraq. 
  During this visit, Wang met with Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister 
Tariq 'Aziz, Foreign Minister Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf and the 
Minister of Industry and Minerals Husayn Kamil Hasan. 
  He also held talks with First Undersecretary of the Iraqi 
Foreign Ministry Abd-el-Gabbar al-Dawri [name as received]. 

</TEXT>

