<H3> <TI>   UK Firm Invests in Jiangsu Province </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UK Firm Invests in Jiangsu Province </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1606120694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1058 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1606120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nanjing, June 16 (XINHUA) -- Inchcape Pacific, part 
of Inchcape, a large international services and marketing group 
based in Britain, has stepped up its drive into China with a 
series of investments in Nanjing, capital of east China's 
Jiangsu Province. 
  The company has acquired a leading motor distribution and 
service company, formed a joint venture to promote sales of 
consumer goods in central China, and established a wholly-owned 
investment holding company. 
  Paul M.F. Cheng, chairman of Inchcape Pacific, said 
yesterday 
at a press conference on the establishment of the three new 
enterprises that China is the number one development priority 
for the Inchcape Group worldwide, and these latest moves in 
Nanjing will help accelerate the growth of the company's 
business in China over the next few years. 
  He noted that Nanjing is an important market in its own 
right. It is the capital of Jiangsu Province, which has a 
population of 69 million people, bigger than Great Britain or 
France. Together with Shanghai and Hangzhou, Nanjing forms a 
strategic hub for Inchcape Pacific's further development in the 
Chang Jiang River basin and deeper into central China. 
  The Inchcape Group operates in over 80 countries. It focuses 
on three main areas: motors, marketing and services. 

</TEXT>

