<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Says Sino-French Ties `Improved Greatly' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng Says Sino-French Ties `Improved Greatly' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1606140894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1337 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1606140894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 16 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng 
said here today that Sino-French relations have improved greatly 
and turned in a new direction since the recent visit to China by 
the French Prime Minister Edouard Balladur. 
  Li made the remarks while meeting this afternoon with 
Jean-Pierre Desgeorges, president of the French-China Committee, 
a French institution designated for promoting trade and economic 
cooperation with China. 
  Desgeorges, once chairman of the French electric company 
Alsthom- Atlantic, has made great efforts to enhance power 
cooperation between China and France. 
  Li expressed his appreciation over the efforts Desgeorges 
and 
other French friends made toward improving bilateral relations 
when the relations met difficulties. 
  On Sino-French economic cooperation, Li said that the two 
countries may increase cooperation on projects with a smaller 
scale of investment besides joining efforts on large projects. 
  Desgeorges said his committee will make greater efforts to 
enhance exchanges and cooperation in the fields of trade and 
economy between France and China. 

