<H3> <TI>   `Voice of China' To Start Broadcasting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Voice of China' To Start Broadcasting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1706084494 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in Chinese 1341 GMT 
16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1706084494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 16 Jun (ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE)--The Voice of 
China of China's Central People's Radio will officially start 
broadcasting from 18 June. Relying on advanced and excellent 
broadcasting equipment and media, its signal can cover Hong 
Kong, Macao, the Zhu Jiang Delta region, and remote islands. 
  Concerned figures of the Central People's Radio said today: 
The Voice of China aims at serving compatriots in Hong Kong and 
Macao and vast numbers of listeners in the Zhu Jiang Delta 
region with timely and accurate news reports, transmission of 
all-round and high-quality information, and varied and colorful 
programs of entertainment and appreciation under the guidance of 
the policy of "one country, two systems" while holding aloft the 
banner of patriotism. 
  It is known that the Voice of China, which merges news and 
information, entertainment, and services into an organic whole, 
will broadcast 21 hours a day, with the focus on three major 
special live programs: The "Golden Channel," a program mainly 
on news, current affairs, and economic and trade information 
service; the "Scenery of China," a program mainly on exhibiting 
China's folk customs; and the "Tender Night of China," a program 
mainly on cultural information and entertainment and 
appreciation. 
  The reception frequency of the Voice of China is: Medium 
wave 1215 kilohertz, FM 104.9 megahertz. 

</TEXT>

