<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Gives Speech at Huangpu Academy Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Gives Speech at Huangpu Academy Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706040194 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0958 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1706040194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Speech by Li Ruihuan at a meeting commemorating the 70th </F>
founding anniversary of the Huangpu (Whampoa) Military Academy 
and the 10th founding anniversary of the Huangpu Alumni 
Association on 16 June 1994] 
  [Text] Beijing, 16 Jun (XINHUA) -- Friends and comrades: 
  Today alumni of the Huangpu Military Academy at home and 
from 
abroad happily gather here to commemorate the academy's 70th 
founding anniversary and the Huangpu Alumni Association's 10th 
founding anniversary. On behalf of the CPC Central Committee, I 
extend warm congratulations and sincere greetings to all Huangpu 
alumni who are present today and through you, to all the 
academy's teachers and cadets at home and abroad. 
  Seven decades ago, Dr. Sun Yat-sen -- the great patriot and 
pioneer of the democratic revolution in China -- summarized 
bitter the experience of repeated setbacks in the pursuit of 
national independence, freedom and democracy, and the people's 
happiness; resolutely reshuffled the Kuomintang [KMT]; and, with 
the support and assistance of the Comintern and the CPC, put 
forward the three major policies on "alliance with Russia and 
the Communists, and assistance to peasants and workers," thereby 
effecting the first cooperation between the KMT and the CPC. In 
order to set up a revolutionary army and use armed revolutionary 
forces to fight against armed counterrevolutionary forces, Dr. 
Sun Yat-sen, together with the Chinese Communists, represented 
by Zhou Enlai, jointly founded the Huangpu Military Academy. 
Imbued with the aspiration of serving the country, ardent young 
people from various parts of the country congregated at 
"revolutionary Huangpu," and one after another groups of 
revolutionary soldiers grew to maturity at the academy, becoming 
the backbone of the Northern Expedition. Noble-minded Huangpu 
cadets from both KMT and CPC waged a bloodbath battle side by 
side to "topple imperialist powers and eliminate warlords," 
thereby defeating the northern reactionary warlords. After the 
Japanese imperialists launched an all-out war of aggression 
against China, which put the Chinese nation at a critical 
juncture between life or death, the KMT and the CPC -- under the 
CPC-sponsored great banner of national united front against 
Japan -- cooperated once again and fought against Japan, thereby 
winning the great victory over foreign aggression. We shall 
forever cherish the memory of those Huangpu martyrs who made 
important contributions to repelling aggressors and safeguarding 
national independence. 
  Seventy years have passed. The CPC and Comrade Mao Zedong 
led the Chinese people in accomplishing the democratic 
revolution, which Dr. Sun Yat-sen did not accomplish; and 
developed it into a socialist revolution. Earthshaking changes 
have taken place on the great earth of the motherland. The 
Chinese nation now stands erect in the east of the world and 
enjoys high esteem in the international community. Today China 
sees vigorous development in all fields of endeavor, and enjoys 
economic prosperity, political stability, national unity, and 
social progress. Guided by Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory of 
building socialism with Chinese characteristics, and led by the 
CPC Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core, the 
Chinese people are seizing the opportunity, deepening reform, 
and opening up wider; and the magnificent ideal of building a 
prosperous, democratic, civilized modern socialist power is 
being gradually transformed into a reality through the great 
efforts of the sons and daughters of the Chinese nation working 
hard in a pioneering spirit. 
  Achieving the motherland's peaceful reunification accords 
with the aspirations of the people and the demand of the nation; 
and it is the sacred mission of the Chinese people of all 
nationalities, including the compatriots in Taiwan. We shall 
continue to promote the cause of peaceful reunification under 
the concept of "one country, two systems." We have time and 
again stated our view that endorsing reunification means loving 
the country; and that differences existing between the two sides 
of the strait can be gradually resolved through increasing 
contacts and consultations under the principle of one China. 
Our stand has been praised and endorsed by farsighted people 
everywhere. We hope that the Taiwan authorities will weigh 
national interests above anything else and take practical 
measures to join us in accomplishing the great cause of 
motherland reunification. 
  Dr. Sun Yat-sen once said: "In reunification lies the hope 
of all countrymen who will enjoy happiness when reunification is 
realized. Failure to accomplish reunification will bring us 
suffering." The late Marshals Xu Xiangqign and Nie Rongzhen 
said in January 1990: "As the motherland has yet to be 
reunified, the alumni need to continue to exert themselves." 
The Huangpu Alumni Association has done tremendous work in 
promoting exchanges and contacts between the two sides of the 
strait in the last 10 years since its founding. We hope that 
you will redouble efforts to score even greater successes in the 
work. May Huangpu alumni on both sides of the strait unite and 
contribute more to the reunification of the motherland and the 
rejuvenation of the Chinese nation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

