<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   More on Huangpu Academy Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More on Huangpu Academy Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1606111094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1047 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1606111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 16 (XINHUA) -- More than 600 people 
gathered here today to mark the 70th anniversary of the founding 
of the influential Huangpu Military Academy. 
  The gathering also marked the 10th anniversary of the 
Huangpu 
Military Academy Alumni Association. 
  Both Chinese president and chairman of the Central Military 
Commission, Jiang Zemin, and vice-chairman of the Central 
Military Commission, Liu Huaqing, calligraphed inscriptions of 
greetings for the anniversaries. 
  Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the 
Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said at the 
gathering that he hoped all alumni across the Taiwan Strait 
would unite for the reunification of the motherland and the 
revitalization of China. 
  Li, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political 
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, said 
that the reunification of the motherland is the common wish and 
sacred duty of the people of all nationalities in China, 
including the Taiwan compatriots. 
  Premier Li Peng and several other senior Chinese leaders, 
met 
the people attending today's gathering. 
  Huangpu (Whampoa) Military Academy, which was established in 
1924 by Dr. Sun Yat-sen at Huangpu near Guangzhou, was a 
training school for officers of the national revolutionary army 
during China's first revolutionary civil war (1924-1927). 
  Li Moan, vice-president of the Huangpu Military Academy 
Alumni Association, urged all who had attended the academy to be 
united under the banner of patriotism and to carry out the 
wishes of Dr. Sun Yat-sen and other revolutionary martyrs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

