<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Forum on Counterfeit Goods Opens in Hangzhou </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Forum on Counterfeit Goods Opens in Hangzhou </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706103694 Hangzhou Zhejiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1706103694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hangzhou Zhejiang People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Li Xiongxiong; from the "Provincial News </F>
Hookup" program] 
  [Text] A national forum on cracking down on counterfeit 
goods opened in Hangzhou today. 
  According to information revealed at the meeting, the State 
Economic and Trade Commission, the State Administration for 
Industry and Commerce, the State Bureau of Technological 
Supervision, as well as public security, supervision, and 
judicial organs are currently making arrangements for a new 
offensive against counterfeiting. Three major campaigns will be 
unfolded across the nation in June, July, and August to smash 
counterfeiting dens, investigate major cases, and rectify the 
market. The national office for cracking down on counterfeiting 
has listed 10 major cases to be intensively investigated and 
dealt with in 1994. Counterfeiting dens that need to be smashed 
as well as counterfeit and shoddy goods markets to be rectified 
and banned have been determined as well. 
  At the national forum, delegates from a dozen or so 
provinces 
and municipalities will hold discussions on the specifics in 
conducting the three major campaigns against counterfeiting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

