<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Implements Measures Accelerating Foreign Trade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai Implements Measures Accelerating Foreign Trade </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706075994 Shanghai People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
2300 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1706075994 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanghai People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "990 Morning News" program] </F>
  [Text] Government departments have enacted and begun 
implementing measures of strategic importance aimed at 
accelerating Shanghai's economic relations and trade with 
foreign countries. Wang Zukang, chairman of the Shanghai 
Municipal Foreign Economic Relations and Trade Commission, 
yesterday briefed the press on the specific measures. 
  Among the specific measures were those calling for 
accelerating implementation of a plan to export leading 
products; for planning a number of major projects and products 
in accordance with Shanghai's overall economic development goals 
and changes in the international market; and for accelerating 
the transformation of foreign trade operational mechanisms. 
Also included were those aimed at focusing on building large 
enterprises and general commercial establishments which combine 
trade, industry, and commerce and which can increase market 
share at home and abroad, as well as those aimed at speeding up 
port construction, improving port functions, and diversifying 
foreign markets. 

</TEXT>

