<H3> <TI>   Jilin's Oil Output Increases in First Quarter </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jilin's Oil Output Increases in First Quarter </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1706053194 Changchun JILIN RIBAO in Chinese 8 June 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK1706053194 </F>
<F P=104>  Changchun JILIN RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary] The Jilin oil field overfulfilled its production 
plan for the first quarter of this year. Its average daily 
output of crude oil in May was 9,060 tonnes and showed a 91 
tonne increase over that of April. The oil field put 33 new oil 
wells into production in April this year, which turned out 100 
tonnes of crude oil as of the end of May. 

</TEXT>

