<F P=100> Northwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qinghai's Import, Use of Foreign Capital Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qinghai's Import, Use of Foreign Capital Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1606104794 Xining Qinghai People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1606104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Xining Qinghai People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Our province has created a new situation in the 
work of importing and using foreign capital. By the end of last 
year, more than 1,000 internal economic cooperation contracts 
had been signed involving more than 300 million yuan, and the 
total amount of direct materials and goods coordination was more 
than 400 million yuan. Eight autonomous prefectures, 
prefectures, and cities throughout the province have established 
or developed cooperative relations with 61 areas outside the 
province based on similar trades and services. 
  Vice Governor Liu Guanghe recently led a Qinghai delegation 
to visit the United States and Canada to invite investments. It 
succeeded in signing a total 12 projects. By the end of May, 
the contracts and regulations of 82 foreign-funded enterprises 
had been examined and approved and they had received their 
approval licenses. In addition, more than $35 million in foreign 
capital had been imported. Of these foreign-funded enterprises, 
70 percent are engaged in the exploitation of natural resources 
and in production involving light industry, textiles, 
electronics, chemistry, building construction, communications, 
metallurgy, nonferrous metal, foodstuffs, agricultural and 
sideline products, and so on. 

</TEXT>

