<F P=100> PRC MEDIA ON TAIWAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Calls For Joint Efforts at Reunification </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Calls For Joint Efforts at Reunification </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706092994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0920 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1706092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 17 (XINHUA) -- A leader of the 
Communist Party of China (CPC) today called for common efforts 
from both sides of the Taiwan Straits toward the goal of China's 
reunification. 
  Li Ruihuan, a Standing Committee member of the Political 
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, reiterated that Taiwan is 
an inseparable part of China's territory and China's 
reunification is the "common wish and noble mission" of all 
Chinese people, including Taiwan compatriots. 
  Li, also chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference, made these remarks 
during a meeting with Ping-ti Ho, vice-president of the National 
Association of Chinese-Americans (of the United States). 
  Li expressed the hope that people from all walks of life on 
both sides of the Taiwan Straits will make joint efforts to 
contribute to the great cause of China's reunification. 
  He also hoped that exchanges and cooperation in economy, 
culture and other aspects across the straits would be 
strengthened. 
  Li expressed appreciations to Ho for his long-time efforts 
in 
promoting Sino-U.S. relations and the exchanges across the 
Taiwan Straits. 
  Wang Zhaoguo, head of the United Front Work Department of 
the 
CPC Central Committee, and Sidney Ho, Ping-ti's son and 
president of Skyho AG, a Swiss company, were present at the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

