<DATE1>  16 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council Denies Reports on Direct Trade With Mainland </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council Denies Reports on Direct Trade With Mainland </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706072794 Taipei Voice of Free China in English 0200 GMT 
16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1706072794 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei Voice of Free China </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Mainland Affairs Council Tuesday [14 June] 
denied reports that Taiwan is preparing to upgrade cross strait 
relations to allow direct trade. 
  According to media reports, the council has churned out a 
document to propose that the government proceed into the second 
phase of the National Reunification Guidelines next year. The 
second phase of the guidelines allows official exchanges in 
direct trade between Taiwan and Mainland China, which are 
currently banned. The first phase currently in effect only 
allows indirect trade and civilian contacts. 
  The media reports said: The council has made a proposal 
anticipating Taiwan will join the General Agreement on Tariff 
and Trade at the end of the year. 
  A council spokesman stressed: Only after Peking recognizes 
Taipei as a political entity and stops isolating Taiwan 
internationally will the government here proceed into the second 
phase of the National Reunification Guidelines. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

