<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Investment Commission Approves 49 Mainland Projects </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Investment Commission Approves 49 Mainland Projects </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706074294 Taipei CNA in English 0702 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1706074294 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Danielle Yang] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, June 17 (CNA) -- The Investment Commission 
approved 49 Taiwan investment projects in Mainland China worth 
NT$1.6 [new Taiwan dollars] billion (U.S.$59 million) during its 
screening meeting Thursday [16 June], indicating that Taiwan's 
investment fever on Mainland China has not cooled. 
  The approval brought the total number of investment projects 
approved since the Qiandao incident to 233, worth more than NT$5 
billion (U.S.$185 million), a commission official said. 
  The Thursday meeting followed a May 27 meeting that approved 
93 investment projects worth NT$1.9 billion (U.S.$70 million). 
  Meanwhile, United Microelectronics Corp. also gained 
approval 
to introduce industrial technical personnel from Mainland China 
to the island. This is the first time a local enterprise is 
being allowed to import mainland expertise to Taiwan, the 
official noted. 

</TEXT>

