approval. 
  The group was led by Major General Lu Zengqi, Chinese 
Government representative and director of the Health Department 
of the General Logistics Department of the Chinese People's 
Liberation Army. 
  The International Committee of Military Medicine, recognized 
by the United Nations, is an inter-governmental organization 
which now has some 100 member countries. 
  The successful bidding for the 1996 venue will facilitate 
military medicine exchanges between China and other member 
countries, sources here said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

