<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Kills Item on Academy, Association Anniversaries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Kills Item on Academy, Association Anniversaries </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Original Version </H4>

<F P=102> OW1706015694 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1158 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1706015694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Sun Yong (1327 0516); Beijing XINHUA Domestic </F>
Service in Chinese at 1503 GMT on 16 June transmits a service 
message replacing the following item] 
  [Text] Beijing, 16 Jun (XINHUA) -- A meeting to mark the 
70th founding anniversary of the Huangpu [Whampoa] Military 
Academy and the 10th anniversary of the Huangpu Military Academy 
Alumni Association took place at the Great Hall of the People 
this afternoon. 
  Li Peng, Hu Jintao, Qian Qichen, Zhang Zhen, Qin Jiwei, 
Cheng 
Siyuan, Li Peiyao, Yang Rudai, Wang Zhaoguo, Ngapoi Ngawang 
Jigmei, Sepydin Aza, Hong Xuezhi, Wan Guoquan and others 
attended the commemorations, or had their pictures taken with 
representatives of the military academy's alumni prior to the 
commemorations. 
  Li Ruihuan addressed the meeting. He began his speech by 
extending the CPC Central Committee's warm greetings and sincere 
regards to the alumni and to the academy's teachers and cadets 
at home and abroad. Li Ruihuan said: Huangpu Military Academy 
was founded 70 years ago by Dr. Sun Yat-sen and Chinese 
communists represented by Zhou Enlai. Now 70 years have gone by 
and the Chinese people led by the CPC and Comrade Mao Zedong 
have accomplished the democratic revolution, which Dr. Sun 
Yat-sen did not accomplish, and developed this revolution into a 
socialist revolution. Achieving our motherland's peaceful 
reunification accords with the will of the people, it is what 
our nation wants, and it is also a sacred mission for Chinese 
people of all nationalities, including our countrymen in Taiwan. 
I hope Huangpu alumni on the two sides of the strait will unite 
and contribute more to our motherland's reunification and 
China's revitalization. (full text of the speech will be 
transmitted separately) 
  Addressing the commemoration, Li Moan, vice president of the 
Huangpu Military Academy Alumni Association, said: In the past 
we joined the whole nation in fighting the big powers and 
eliminating the warlords. Earthshaking changes have now taken 
place in our great motherland, and people throughout the country 
are advancing triumphantly under the guidance of Comrade Deng 
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics. Since its founding 10 years ago, the Huangpu 
Military Academy Alumni Association has been making unswerving 
efforts to foster the academy's spirit, establish ties with 
alumni, promote the motherland's reunification, and to dedicate 
itself to revitalizing China. Our association has already 
established contacts with nearly 1,000 alumni in Taiwan as well 
as alumni in more than 10 countries and regions. When 
contacting alumni in Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macao, and overseas 
areas, our association has seized every opportunity to expound 
the nation's policy toward Taiwan -- a policy characterized by 
"peaceful reunification; and one country, two systems." We have 
also done many things useful for the introduction of capital, 
technology, and proficient personnel; and for promoting the 
development of relations and exchanges between the two sides of 
the strait. 
  Zhou Lejun, a Huangpu alumnus from Taiwan, also addressed 
the 
occasion. He said: The meritorious services which Huangpu 
alumni performed during the eastern and northern expeditions and 
the War of Resistance Against Japan have gone down in history. 
We are pleased to note the exchanges between alumni on the two 
sides of the strait today. We should broaden our vision and, as 
brothers, we should by no means be engaged in quarrel. We are 
absolutely against separation; and even more so are we against 
intervention by foreign forces and the obstruction of our great 
motherland's reunification. I hope Huangpu alumni will work hard 
together so that the great cause of reunification can be 
achieved at an early date. 
  The commemoration meeting was called by the Chinese People's 
Political Consultative Conference [CPPCC] National Committee. 
Ye Xuanping, vice chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, 
chaired the meeting, which was attended by Huangpu alumni at 
home and from abroad and people of all walks of life in Beijing 
-- more than 500 in total. 
  In the evening, the CPPCC National Committee and the CPC 
Central Committee United Front Department hosted a banquet at 
the Great Hall of the People to mark the 70th founding 
anniversary of the Huangpu Military Academy and the 10th 
anniversary of the Huangpu Military Academy Alumni Association. 
Wang Zhaoguo delivered a toast at the banquet. 

</TEXT>

