<H3> <TI>   Zou Jiahua Inspects Communications Center </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zou Jiahua Inspects Communications Center </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1606161994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1457 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1606161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 16 (XINHUA) -- Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua 
this afternoon made an inspection of the Beijing International 
Telecommunications Center and an experimental base of the 
Ministry of Railways. 
  Zou, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Central 
Committee of the Communist Party of China, visited some parts of 
the telecommunications center, including a wireless and digital 
optic-fiber, high-frequency system and an international 
telephone exchange center. 
  The center, set up in 1987, is an important link in China's 
national telecommunications network which transmits 
international telephone, telegraph and electronic data into or 
out of China. 
  Zou asked about the center's operation and encouraged staff 
to keep China in the sector's forefront. 
  On his tour of the base in the Science Research Institute 
under the Ministry of Railways, Zou boarded an in-trial 
para-high-speed train, which will run from Guangzhou, capital of 
south China's Guangdong Province, to Shenzhen, China's boomtown 
in the reform drive. 
  The passenger train, made entirely in China, is designed to 
run 180 kilometers per hour and is equipped with air 
conditioning in every car. 
  Zou discussed technological and management issues with 
engineers at the base. 

</TEXT>

