<H3> <TI>   DPRK: France `Aggravating Situation' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK: France `Aggravating Situation' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1906053694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0427 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1906053694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["France Accused of Aggravating Situation on Korean </F>
Peninsula"] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 19 (XINHUA) -- The Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) Saturday [18 June] accused 
France of aggravating the situation on the Korean peninsula by 
supporting sanctions against the DPRK, the local newspaper 
NODONG SINMUN reported today. 
  It was reported that the French Foreign Ministry recently 
favored a decisive measure against the DPRK and manifested its 
official stand to support a UN resolution on sanctions. 
  "Such moves of France are aimed at preventing the 'nuclear 
issue' which has become an international focal point from being 
solved through DPRK-U.S. talks... goading Northeast Asian 
countries onto a conflict and thereby fishing in troubled 
waters," the paper quoted a spokesman of the DPRK Foreign 
Ministry as saying. 
  "The situation in our country now has become extremely 
tense," he said, adding that "our people are making full 
prepartions to defend the dignity and sovereignty of the 
country." 
  "We have already declared more than once that in case any 
'sanctions' should be imposed on us, not only the parties taking 
the van in enforcing them but also those who back them would be 
held responsible," the spokesman noted. 
  "The French authorities must know that our warning is not an 
empty word," he warned. 
  The spokesman pointed out that as a permanent member of the 
UN Security Council, France "should help toward a peaceful 
solution to the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula through 
dialogue and negotiation." 

</TEXT>

