<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Urgent Problems' Cause Cancellation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Urgent Problems' Cause Cancellation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706123094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1042 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1706123094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 17 (XINHUA) -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin cancelled his scheduled meeting today with visiting 
Vietnamese Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet because he has to deal 
with some "urgent problems," a high-ranking Kremlin official 
said. 
  The official said that "there are no politics behind the 
cancelled meeting," according to the ITAR-TASS NEWS AGENCY. 
  The Russian president "has to solve urgent problems which 
have accumulated during the three days of his absence from 
Moscow," the official explained. 
  He said that the meeting was planned only in a preliminary 
way, adding that "as far as the Russian-Vietnamese documents are 
signed at the level and upon mutual agreement of the prime 
ministers of both countries, Boris Yeltsin, who has been absent 
from Moscow for three days, is busy with urgent state affairs 
today." [sentence as received] 
  Yeltsin spent three days touring the Russian Far East and 
returned to Moscow on Thursday. 

</TEXT>

