<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Comparison to Jiang Zemin Meets Russian Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Comparison to Jiang Zemin Meets Russian Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2705192794 </F>
<F P=103> OW2705192794 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese at 1356 GMT on 
27 May carries a report on Jiang Zemin meeting with Russian 
Prime Minister Chernomyrdin in Beijing on 27 May. 
  The XINHUA Chinese version has been compared to the XINHUA 
English version entitled "Jiang Zemin Meets Russian Prime 
Minister" published in the 31 May China DAILY REPORT on pages 9 
and 10 and was found to contain the following variations: 
  Page 9, column two, subslug reads: ...[By reporter Yang 
Guojun (2799 0948 6874)] ... (adding subslug) 
  Page 10, column one, first full paragraph, only sentence 
reads: ...V.S. Chernomyrdin at Zhongnanhai this afternoon [27 
May]. [new graf] 
  Jiang Zemin first expressed his warm welcome to Prime 
Minister Chernomyrdin on his visit. The bilateral relations... 
(supplying location and time of meeting, adding additional 
sentence) 
  Column one, paragraph eight, only sentence reads: ...to the 
long-term, stable, good-neighborly, and mutually-beneficial... 
(adding word "stable") 
  Column two, first paragraph, only sentence reads: ...the 
meeting with President Yeltsin. Jiang Zemin asked Prime 
Minister Chernomyrdin to convey his regards to President Yeltsin 
when he returns home. 
  The meeting, which lasted more than one hour, was held amid 
a 
cordial and friendly atmosphere. 
  Among those at the meeting from the Chinese side were Qian 
Qichen, vice premier and foreign minister; Jing Shuping, 
chairman of the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce; 
He Guangyuan, chairman of the Government Reception Committee and 
minister of Machine-Building Industry; Dai Bingguo, vice 
minister of Foreign Affairs; and Shi Guangsheng, vice minister 
of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation. 
  Present at the meeting from the Russian side were Deputy 
Prime Minister Aleksandr Shokhin, Minister of Protection of 
Environment and Natural Resources Danilov-Danilyan, Minister of 
Transportation Yefimov, Minister of Agriculture and Food 
Khlystun, Chairman of the Committee for Fisheries (Kuriliskiy), 
and Deputy Defense Minister Kokoshin. (adding sentence and new 
paragraphs) 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

