<H3> <TI>   Economics Minister Wang Zhongyu Meets Kim Yong-sam </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economics Minister Wang Zhongyu Meets Kim Yong-sam </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706143894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0241 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1706143894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, 15 June (XINHUA) -- ROK President Kim 
Yong-sam met with Wang Zhongyu, Chinese chairman of the PRC-ROK 
Industrial Cooperation Committee and minister in charge of the 
State Economic and Trade Commission of China who is currently on 
a visit here, at the presidential palace this afternoon. 
  Kim Yong-sam expressed admiration for the achievements in 
China's economic development. He also said: Our two economies 
are highly complementary; leaders of our two countries have 
reached a consensus on strengthening our industrial cooperation. 
Our two countries will carry out cooperation in the automobile 
industry, civil aviation industrial technology, 
program-controlled interchange, high- definition television, and 
other fields. This will have a significant impact on the 
economic development of both the ROK and China. 
  Wang Zhongyu, who is leading a delegation to the PRC-ROK 
Industrial Cooperation Committee's first meeting that opened 
today, arrived here on 12 June. The delegation will leave for 
home on 17 June. 

</TEXT>

