<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   All Khmer Rouge Representatives To Leave Phnom Penh 19 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    All Khmer Rouge Representatives To Leave Phnom Penh 19 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1906142194 Beijing China Radio International in Cambodian 
1030 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1906142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing China Radio International </F>
<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Democratic Kampuchea [DK] representative in 
Phnom Penh announced on 18 June that Chan Youran, DK Party's 
representative to the meeting of the Phnom Penh Roundtable 
Commission, and his assistants left Phnom Penh by plane on the 
morning of 18 June. All other officials of the DK 
Representative's Office will be leaving Phnom Penh on 19 June at 
the demand of the Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC]'s Ministry 
of Interior. 
  On the night of 17 June, DK Chairman Khieu Samphan sent an 
urgent telegram to His Majesty King Norodom Sihanouk informing 
him of the Ministry of Interior's demand that all DK 
representatives leave Phnom Penh. 
  On the morning of 18 June, His Majesty King Norodom Sihanouk 
sent a reply calling on DK representatives to quickly leave 
Phnom Penh to avoid any incident that might lead to the 
deterioration of the situation. In his reply, the King also 
said that he would maintain good relations with Mr. Khieu 
Samphan and the DK Party as before. 
  On the night of 17 June, the RGC Ministry of Interior issued 
an expulsion order released through radio and television, saying 
that due to the failure of the 15-16 June meeting of the Phnom 
Penh Roundtable Commission, the DK representatives and staff 
must leave Phnom Penh before 19 June because the Ministry of 
Interior might not be able to provide security for them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

