<H3> <TI>   Filipino Vice President Estrada Leaves for Beijing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Filipino Vice President Estrada Leaves for Beijing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1806031294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0233 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1806031294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Manila, June 18 (XINHUA) -- Philippine Vice 
President Joseph Estrada left here this morning for Beijing on a 
nine-day official visit to China at the invitation of Chinese 
Vice President Rong Yiren. 
  The vice president told XINHUA at the airport that he hopes 
his first visit to China will help cement closer relations 
between the two countries, particularly in cultural and economic 
fields. 
  During his stay in China, he said, the two sides are 
expected 
to sign a cultural agreement. 
  Estrada was born in Manila on April 19, 1937. As a former 
action movie star, he is very popular in the country. 
  He was chosen as one of the "ten outstanding young men in 
public administration" in 1972. 
  Having been the mayor of San Juan for 16 years, he was 
elected senator in 1987 and became vice president in 1992. 
Subsequently, he was designed by President Ramos as chairman of 
the Presidential Anti-Crime Commission. 

</TEXT>

