<F P=104>  Hangzhou Zhejiang People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Provincial News Hookup" program] </F>
  [Text] The seventh standing committee meeting of the 
Seventh Zhejiang Provincial Committee of the Chinese People's 
Political Consultative Conference [CPPCC] was held in Hangzhou 
today. Liu Feng and Chen Fawen, respectively chairman and vice 
chairman of the provincial CPPCC committee, presided over the 
morning plenary session. Participants adopted the meeting's 
schedule and agenda. According to the agenda, the meeting will 
discuss further strengthening Zhejiang's socialist spiritual 
civilization, offer relevant opinions and suggestions, and 
invite leaders from the departments concerned to give briefings 
on Zhejiang's progress in promoting socialist spiritual 
civilization, in implementing nine-year compulsory education, 
and in launching an anticorruption campaign to foster honesty, 
as well as on the status of public order in Zhejiang. It will 
also discuss and approve proposals to be forwarded to the 
provincial government, as well as personnel matters. 
  In the morning, (Shen Hui), deputy director of the 
provincial 
party committee's propaganda department; (Zhu Yaozu), deputy 
secretary of the provincial discipline inspection commission; 
and (Cai Yangmeng), deputy director of the provincial public 
security department, reported to the standing committee members 
on Zhejiang's progress in promoting socialist spiritual 
civilization and in launching an anticorruption campaign to 
foster honesty, as well as on the status of public order in 
Zhejiang. Sun Jiaxian, Wu Renyuan, Zhan Shaowen, Ding Deyun, 
Xue Yanzhuang, Que Duanlin, Zhang Kejian, and Wang Xixuan, vice 
chairmen of the provincial CPPCC committee, attended the 
meeting, as did (Li Qing), secretary general of the provincial 
CPPCC committee. Wang Qidong, vice chairman of the provincial 
people's congress standing committee, attended the meeting by 
invitation. Present at the meeting in observer status were 
veteran comrades (Mao Jiehua) and Shang Jingcai; Sun Yannian, 
member of the national CPPCC committee standing committee; and 
some national CPPCC committee members in Hangzhou. 

</TEXT>

