<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Verdicts Delivered in Zhejiang's Qiandao Lake Trial </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Verdicts Delivered in Zhejiang's Qiandao Lake Trial </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Three Receive Death Sentence </H4>

<F P=102> OW1906083994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0334 
GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1906083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, June 19 (XINHUA) -- The Hangzhou City 
Intermediate People's Court [IPC] convened a sentencing rally in 
Hangzhou this morning to announce the judgment of the Zhejiang 
Provincial Higher People's Court approving the death sentence 
for Wu Lihong, Hu Zhihan, and Yu Aijun, the three criminals 
guilty of the heinous crime of robbery and murder in Qiandao 
Lake, Chunan County, on 31 March. Leaders of Hangzhou city and 
representatives from all walks of life and relevant departments 
of the province and city -- 1,200 in all -- were present at the 
sentencing rally. 
  Yang Gang, president of the Hangzhou City IPC, presided over 
the rally. Wang Zhijian, chief judge of the First Criminal 
Division of the Hangzhou City IPC, read the adjudication. After 
reviewing the death sentences, the Zhejiang Provincial Higher 
People's Court decided to approve the sentences -- death and 
deprivation of political rights for life -- for Wu Lihong, Hu 
Zhihan, and Yu Aijun for the crime of robbery and murder. The 
court decided the cumulative punishment of death and deprivation 
of political rights for life be carried out. 
  Wang Yongming, mayor of Hangzhou, spoke at the rally. He 
pointed out that the sentencing rally fully reflects the purpose 
of judicial organs in upholding justice and being loyal to the 
law and people. It fully reflects the party and government's 
firm determination to safeguard public order, to severely punish 
criminals, and to protect the safety of life and property of the 
broad masses of the people as well as compatriots from Hong 
Kong, Macao and Taiwan, and overseas Chinese, and foreign 
nationals within Chinese territory. The severe punishment for 
the three criminals in accordance with law not only defends the 
dignity of law but also serves as the best consolation for the 
deceased compatriots. 
  After the sentencing rally, the three criminals Wu Lihong, 
Hu 
Zhihan, and Yu Aijun were, after verification of their identity, 
escorted to the execution ground and shot in pursuance of an 
order of execution issued by the president of the Zhejiang 
Provincial Higher People's Court. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-26152 </DOCNO>
