<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Verdicts Delivered in Zhejiang's Qiandao Lake Trial </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Verdicts Delivered in Zhejiang's Qiandao Lake Trial </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    1,200 Gather To Hear Judgment </H4>

<F P=102> OW1906042894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0355 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1906042894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, June 19 (XINHUA) -- Three men guilty of 
robbery and murder in the March 31 Qiandao Lake tragedy in 
Zhejiang Province, east China, were executed here today after 
the provincial higher court approved the death sentence. 
  More than 1,200 people gathered at the Hangzhou theater this 
morning to hear the judgement announced by the Intermediate 
People's Court of Hangzhou. The verdict was read by the 
intermediate people's court, saying that Wu Lihong, Hu Zhihan 
and Yu Aijun on March 31 this year robbed and murdered 24 Taiwan 
tourists and eight mainland crew members on a pleasure boat on 
Qingdao Lake, a major tourist attraction in Zhejiang Province. 
  It said that the three men robbed the tourists of large 
quantities of their property by threatening them with violence 
and then murdered the victims by blowing up the boat and setting 
fire to it. 
  The three men accused of robbery and murder were sentenced 
to 
death and deprived of political rights for life on June 12. 
  They did not appeal to a higher court against the sentence 
within the legal period. Chinese law grants a three-day period 
for appeals. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

