<H3> <TI>   Zhejiang Leases Land for Foreign Investment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhejiang Leases Land for Foreign Investment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2006030394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0147 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2006030394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, June 20 (XINHUA) -- East China's Zhejiang 
Province has leased five plots of land for foreign investment. 
  With a combined area of 23.7 sq km, the five plots are 
located in the Ningbo Bonded Zone, Hangzhou's Qianjiang 
Investment Zone, Zhoushan's Donggang Economic Development Zone, 
the Jiaxing Economic Development Zone and the Zhapu Economic 
Development Zone. 
  The plots are being developed jointly by the Zhejiang Real 
Estate Industrial Development Company and five other companies. 
  Altogether, 300 million yuan has been used in constructing 
infrastructure facilities, and seven sq km of the areas are 
ready for foreign investment. 
  An official of the company said that business people from 
the 
United States, Canada and Australia have expressed interest in 
investing in the areas. 

</TEXT>

